'''TEOTWAWKI''' is an [[acronym]] standing for "'''T'''he '''E'''nd '''O'''f '''T'''he '''W'''orld '''A'''s '''W'''e '''K'''now '''I'''t". The acronym is spoken “Tee-ought-walk-ee”. It is used often online by members of [[survivalist]] groups, but has spread into common usage. It is particularly used by those who believe that a hypothesized energy crisis commonly called [[Peak Oil]] has begun. Since energy is the basis for life, and cheap energy (ancient sunlight per Thom Hartmann) is the foundation of civilization, TEOTWAWKI is predicted to occur as various peaks of productions in [[oil]], natural gas, [[coal]] and even [[soil]] fertility occur.  Fatalists as well as survivalists are discussing this on the web.  Some such as Richard Duncan suggest that an even more important peak has occurred - the peak of energy produced per capita. He predicts that we are on the downward side and that the electric grid may soon collapse ([[Olduvai theory]]) and with it civilization as we know it.  
  
See also [[End of the world]].

